This is a customary formula in all cases of security given to the state, and commonly limited to such cases by the words publice, in publicum, or populo. The praedes, written proevidee in the lex cararia, were the sureties who were bound over3 they were to be landowners, and their pradia (praehendia) might be eeized upon in case 01 default (ea pignore data publice mancipio fidem praestant. Varro 1.1. v, 40).
